				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">Gekko wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Also, should I add a<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">LDA #$BBAA<br />CMP $2140<br />BEQ $02 ;Skip the PLP and RTL or RTS<br />PLP<br />RTL ;or RTS</div><br />between the REP #$30 and the SEP #$20?<br /></div><br />I'd highly suspect a 16-bit access won't work, as the port is <em>probably</em> an 8-bit link between the chips.</div>
<br />
<br />The CMP in question would actually read 8 bits from $2140 (APU_PORT_0) and $2141 (APU_PORT_1).  So the ""16-bit read"" method should work just fine.  The official developers manual even uses to this method in example SPC bootloader code; see Section D.4 (of manual revision A, dated 1992/05/01).
<br />
<br />And yes, you should wait for APU_PORT_0==$AA and APU_PORT_1==$BB before doing transferring any data to/from the SPC.</div>

