				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It doesn't take the S-SMP long to clear 240 bytes of stack and signal to the S-CPU that it's ready. Clearing all of WRAM / VRAM gives you plenty of time for it to finish its setup process.
<br />
<br />Still, it's good advice. For a one-time check, especially for a library routine, it's best to just add the cmp #$bbaa. Never know when someone might call it right off the bat.</div>

